ENTRY            A0120   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
SUBENT        A0120001   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                 12         23
TITLE      Measurement and analysis of the angular distribution
           and effective cross section of the F-19(p,alpha)O-16
           reaction in the energy range 0.4 to 0.72 MeV
AUTHOR     (G.Breuer)
INSTITUTE  (2GERHAM) Physikalischen Staatsinstitut, Hamburg
REFERENCE  (J,ZP,154,339,1959) On German
SAMPLE     The target - Ca-F2 on 10 um aluminium backing.
           Thickness: 28 keV for 340 keV protons.
FACILITY   (ACCEL,2GERGER) Utrecht cascade generator.
DETECTOR   (PLATE) Fifteen nuclear emulsions ( 1. x 4/3 inch)
           are placed round the target at 15. degr. intervals in a
           cylindrical aluminium plate-holder. Ilford C2 emulsions
           are used of 50, 100, or 200 um thickness.
METHOD     (SITA,BCINT)
REL-REF    (I,,P.M.Endt+,J,PHY,18,399,1952) - Experim. equipment
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) total error
           (ERR-S,1.,2.) Statistical error
ADD-RES    (STRUC)
